"title": "7392: lots, casting of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7392: lots, casting of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A means of determining the will of God, prior to the giving of the Holy Spirit at Pentecost. The casting of lots was also used by pagans for the same purpose. Such use reflects the belief that nothing occurred by chance.</p>\n<h2>Casting lots to determine the will of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:33\">PRO 16:33</a></strong></p>\n<h3>In the ministry of the high priest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:30\">EXO 28:30</a></strong> <em>The “Urim and Thummim” were sacred lots maintained for the purpose of determining God's will.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7-Lev8:9\">LEV 8:7–8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:6-Lev16:10\">LEV 16:6–16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:21\">NUM 27:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:8\">DEU 33:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:6\">1SA 28:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:63\">EZR 2:63</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:65\">NEH 7:65</a></p>\n<h3>To apportion land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:54\">NUM 33:54</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:54-Num26:56\">NUM 26:54–26:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:2\">JOS 14:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:10\">JOS 18:10</a></p>\n<h3>To select individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:41-1Sam14:42\">1SA 14:41–14:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:14-Josh7:18\">JOS 7:14–7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:9-Judg20:10\">JDG 20:9–20:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:20-1Sam10:21\">1SA 10:20–10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:7\">JON 1:7</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:15-Acts1:26\">ACT 1:15–1:26</a></strong></p>\n<h3>To assign priestly duties</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr24:5\">1CH 24:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:12-1Chr26:13\">1CH 26:12–26:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:34\">NEH 10:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:8-Luke1:9\">LUK 1:8–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>To settle disputes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:18\">PRO 18:18</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Casting lots as a means of divination</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:21-Ezek21:22\">EZK 21:21–21:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:7\">EST 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:24-Esth9:27\">EST 9:24–9:27</a> <em>The word “purim” is the plural of “pur” and means “lots”.</em></p>\n<h2>Casting lots as a means of distributing plunder</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:2-Joel3:3\">JOL 3:2–3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:10\">NAM 3:10</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:35\">MAT 27:35</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:24\">MRK 15:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:24\">JHN 19:24</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:18\">PSA 22:18</a></p>",
